<subSubSection id="CCFD0CC3FFEF015363A5F28492148859" pageId="13" pageNumber="36" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="84585F48FFEF015363A5F28492148859" blockId="13.[151,760,644,891]" pageId="13" pageNumber="36">
<emphasis id="B693835AFFEF015363A5F284926E89B9" bold="true" box="[151,287,644,667]" pageId="13" pageNumber="36">Comments.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="43E724CBFFEF01536218F284913B89B9" authorityName="Medvedev" authorityYear="2004" box="[298,586,644,667]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Epaenidea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="indochinensis">
<emphasis id="B693835AFFEF01536218F284913B89B9" box="[298,586,644,667]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="36">Epaenidea indochinensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described based on six specimens. I examined one badly damaged 
<typeStatus id="5B5CE1EAFFEF015363A5F2C4938389F9" box="[151,242,708,731]" pageId="13" pageNumber="36">paratype</typeStatus>
(probably female) deposited in the NHMB. Pavel Romantsov kindly provided me with photographs of the 
<typeStatus id="5B5CE1EAFFEF015363A5F30493858839" box="[151,244,772,795]" pageId="13" pageNumber="36">holotype</typeStatus>
deposited in the collection of L. Medvedev. The metasternal process is clearly visible on the photograph of the ventral side and thus 
<taxonomicName id="43E724CBFFEF0153628AF34491168879" authorityName="Medvedev" authorityYear="2004" box="[440,615,836,859]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Epaenidea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="indochinensis">
<emphasis id="B693835AFFEF0153628AF34491168879" box="[440,615,836,859]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="36">E. indochinensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is transferred here to 
<taxonomicName id="43E724CBFFEF015363D5F364922F8859" authorityName="Thunberg" authorityYear="1814" box="[231,350,868,891]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Taumacera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B693835AFFEF015363D5F364922F8859" box="[231,350,868,891]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="36">Taumacera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
